long_desc.thetext:
"Page zoom" was a badly designed and implemented feature in IE7. With IE8 it is to be replaced with "Adaptive Zoom", see http://blogs.msdn.com/ie/archive/2008/03/25/internet-explorer-8-and-adaptive-zoom.aspx .
Check if the previous IE7 pagezoom problems are gone with IE8. Also see bug 1480 for more background info.

The "Page zoom" has the same bad behavior like the IE7, when IE8 is running in Quirks or in IE7 Standard mode. So qooxdoo 0.7.x and 0.8 (trunk) doesn't work with "Page zoom" in Quirks or in IE7 Standard mode.
Qooxdoo 0.7.x doesn't work with "Page zoom" in IE8 Standard mode, because it is always rendered in Quirks mode.
It seems to me, that Oooxdoo 0.8 (trunk) works with "Page zoom" in IE8 Standard mode. But it should be tested again, because the IE8 beta 2 has some rendering issues, see bug 1434 for more details.
Appendix: Qooxdoo 0.8 (trunk) has currently some problems with positioning images in IE8 Standard mode. See screenshot.
Created attachment 392 Screenshot IE8 standard mode
To be checked, now that IE8 RC1 is available.

The "Adaptive Zoom" has problems with scaling. For example the grid layout, the new calculated size isn't correct so small line are always visible. The screenshot from a grid layout shows the problem. I tested the zoom feature with other browsers FF 3 and Safari 3.2.2 and they have the same issue with the grid layout.

Shows the scaling issue with the grid layout
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
